        "assistant": "Based on the canonical definition, **YON differs from Markdown mainly in intent, structure, and machine-actionability**.\n\n| Feature | YON | Markdown |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Primary purpose** | Notation for **AI cognition** and structured processing | Lightweight markup for **human-readable documents** |\n| **Parsing model** | **Stream-first**: each line is a self-contained record | Document-oriented: meaning often depends on surrounding lines |\n| **Grammar** | Fixed minimal grammar with pluggable domain vocabularies | Informal/lightweight markup with many dialects and extensions |\n| **Unit of meaning** | A line/record that can be parsed, validated, or acted on immediately | A paragraph, heading, list, code block, table, etc. inside a larger document |\n| **Error isolation** | Bad records can be isolated line by line | Malformed structure can affect how later text is interpreted |\n| **Audience** | Designed for AI/system consumption first | Designed for human reading and HTML/document rendering |\n| **Domain semantics** | Explicitly supplied through vocabularies | Usually implicit in prose, headings, labels, or conventions |\n| **Actionability** | Intended to support parsing, validation, and execution as data arrives | Mostly descriptive/presentational; not inherently executable or validated |\n\nIn short:\n\n> **Markdown is a human-friendly document notation. YON is a stream-first cognitive record notation.**\n\nMarkdown is good for things like:\n\n```markdown\n# Task\n\nClassify the following sentence as positive or negative.\n\n- Input: I loved the movie.\n- Label: positive\n```\n\nThat is readable to humans, but the structure is partly conventional. A parser has to infer meaning from headings, bullets, indentation, and prose.\n\nYON, by contrast, is designed so that each line is a structured record that can stand alone and be processed immediately. So where Markdown organizes readable documents, **YON organizes machine-usable cognitive events or statements in a stream**.\n\nThe key distinction:\n\n> **Markdown formats thought for readers; YON encodes thought for parsers, validators, and AI systems.**",
