        "assistant": "Based on the canonical definition, **YON differs from a prompt template language in role and level of abstraction**.\n\nA **prompt template language** is mainly a way to generate prompts by filling variables into reusable text patterns.\n\n**YON**, by contrast, is a **stream-first notation for AI cognition**: it defines line-based cognitive records with a fixed minimal grammar and pluggable vocabularies.\n\n| Feature | YON | Prompt template language |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Primary purpose** | Represent structured cognitive records | Generate prompts from reusable templates |\n| **Core unit** | Self-contained line/record | Template with placeholders |\n| **Parsing model** | Stream-first; each line can be parsed as it arrives | Usually rendered as a full prompt before use |\n| **Structure** | Fixed minimal grammar + domain vocabulary | Text plus variables, conditionals, loops, or formatting rules |\n| **Output target** | Machine-parseable/actionable records | Human/LLM-readable prompt text |\n| **Validation** | Records can be validated against vocabulary/schema-like rules | Validation usually checks missing variables or template syntax |\n| **Failure mode addressed** | Avoids block-format fragility by making records independent | Helps reuse prompts but does not inherently solve stream parsing or record isolation |\n| **Relationship to AI cognition** | Intended to encode cognition directly | Intended to instruct or condition an AI system |\n\nIn short:\n\n> **A prompt template language helps you write prompts. YON helps you encode cognitive records.**\n\nFor example, a prompt template might look like:\n\n```text\nClassify the following text as {{label_set}}:\n\n{{input_text}}\n```\n\nIts job is to produce a prompt after substitution.\n\nYON would instead aim to represent the task, input, assertion, observation, decision, or action as structured records that can be parsed independently as they arrive.\n\nSo the key distinction is:\n\n> **Prompt templates are prompt-generation tools; YON is a stream-first cognitive notation.**\n\nThey could also be complementary: a prompt template could emit YON, or YON records could be used as inputs to a prompt-rendering system.",
